["Edward Colston House, also known as Medway, is a historic home located at Falling Waters, Berkeley County, West Virginia. It was built about 1798 and is a two-story, three-bay, gable-roofed frame dwelling.  The two-story, three-bay, gable-roofed frame wing was added about 1900. It is a rare 18th-century frame building and representative of the transition from the Georgian to Federal style.[2]","It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 2003.[1]","This article about a property in Berkeley County, West Virginia on the National Register of Historic Places is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it."]